SIMPLE: umbo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Umbo
<hw>Um"bo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Umbones</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Umbos</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The boss of a shield, at or near the
middle, and usually projecting, sometimes in a sharp spike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A boss, or rounded elevation, or a corresponding
depression, in a palate, disk, or membrane; <as>as, the <ex>umbo</ex> in
the integument of the larvae of echinoderms or in the tympanic membrane
of the ear</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the lateral prominences
just above the hinge of a bivalve shell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umbonated</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Umbonate</ent>⟦br⟧
